    "key_findings": [
        "The study elucidated seven cryo-EM structures of 5-HT2AR in complex with various psychedelic and non-psychedelic agonists, revealing common and distinct molecular interaction motifs for different chemotypes.",
        "It identified that the tryptamine ligands, including DMT, bind in the canonical orthosteric pocket, validating decades of prior biochemical and computational models for ligand interactions.",
        "The work established that an arrestin-biased agonist (RS130-180), solved as part of this study but not in 9AS1, stabilizes a novel non-canonical receptor state, potentially explaining its signaling bias and offering insights into selective drug design."
